Pay attention to the way you move - not just in the poses but in the transitions as well. 

Circling back to the intention behind the movement will allow you to create a meaningful relationship with your body and breath both on and off your mat. 

For me, this type of work allows me to let go of stress, tension and worry. This ensures that I am not carrying around a bunch of weight I do not need to bear. 

Marry the strength with the graceâ€¦

the effort with the ease. 

Finesse > Force.

Hi Adriene!
I've been a big fan for a few years now. Your videos have helped me develop a regular yoga practice and honestly, it has helped me get though some of the hardest times in my life. So thank you so much for that and for your commitment to continuing to bring yoga and amazing teachings to people like you do! I do have one small critique or maybe more of a request. Often in your videos you say things like "guys and girls" or "ladies and gentlemen" or (as in this one) "dudes and dudettes." And while I appreciate the inclusivity, some people are still left out in those types of comments. People like me whose gender identity is non-binary, or other trans and genderqueer people who may be in transition or just don't identify with the idea of a gender binary. So I guess I was wondering if you could maybe change your language a little bit to be more inclusive of people who are somewhere other than male or female on the gender spectrum? Thanks!
